verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Swift to its close ebbs our life’s little day.
Earth’s joys grow dim; its glories pass away.
Change and decay in all around I see;
O Thou, who changest not, abide with me.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}I fear no foe, with Thee at hand to bless;
Ills have no weight, and tears no bitterness,
Where is death’s sting? Where, grave, thy victory?
I triumph still, if Thou abide with me.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Hold thou thy cross before my closing eyes;
Shine thru’ the gloom and point me to the skies.
Heav’ns morning breaks, and earth’s vain shadows flee.
In life, in death, O Lord, abide with me.{/lang-eng}
